<tr><td bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>
<center><strong>Ward Undead</strong></center>
</font></td></tr>
</table></center>
<table width=70%>
<tr><td>Mana:</td>
<td>30</td></tr>
<tr><td>Skill:</td>
<td>Evocation</td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top>
Classes:</td>
<td>
<a href="/spells/cleric.shtml">
Cleric</a>
 (5)<BR>
<a href="/spells/necromancer.shtml">
Necromancer</a>
 (8)<BR>
<a href="/spells/paladin.shtml">
Paladin</a>
 (15)<BR>
<a href="/spells/shadow_knight.shtml">
Shadow Knight</a>
 (22)<BR>
</td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top>Items:</td>
<td>
<a href="/weapons/2h_blunt.shtml#bonethunder_staff">Bonethunder Staff</a><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>Buyable:</td><td>
Yes</td></tr>
<tr><td>Researchable:</td><td>
No</td></tr>
<tr><td>Drops from MOB:</td><td>
No</td></tr>
<tr><td>Cast Time:</td>
<td>2.10 seconds</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2><br></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>Description:</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>
Deals up to 41 damage to target.</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>
<BR>1 tick = 6 seconds<BR>
When a range of effects are given, it usually means that the effect becomes more potent as the caster increases in levels.
