<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Halobash</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-03 15:46:44</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>As a Dwarven Cleric of 10th season I was able to hit Skeleton Pawns at Chessboard for 39 points of damage consistently.  When I rose to 11th season, I was then maxing out the damage at 41 points.  My evoke and channeling skill were always maxed to the highest that it could be for every given level.  Skeletons can resist, and it is very important to time your spells so they do not get interrupted.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Shadow Knight</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-15 14:10:13</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>When i go out collecting bones for my pet spell this spell works great on zombies and skeletons. Although we shadow knights only get this spell at lev 22. I wouldent use this on a spector and then again if i saw a spector i would run unless i had back up and at higher levels. Useing this on a ghoul can help some but ghouls are a little tough until certain levels. Use your better judgement with this spell although i wouldent rely on it.  (A KNIGHT OF THE SHADOWS OF NIGHT KEEP)</font></td></tr></table>
