<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: evilsofa</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-14 17:38:11</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>For necromancers and it seems everyone else, this is the first spell that uses the evocation skill.  Thus, when you first get it, it will fizzle like crazy.  Do NOT despair of this though - this is a necromancer's BEST level 8 spell, along with Bone Walk for their new pet.<BR>
<BR>
I spent my entire DE Necro's 8th level taking down skeletons with Ward Undead.  By the time I was done, I'd gotten my necro up to level 9, maxed out the evocation to 50 so that Ward Undead usually works, brought in about 10 or 20 pp worth of loot, and 4 stacks of those precious bone chips (necros should NEVER EVER sell bone chips, no matter how much they are going for!)<BR>
<BR>
Two hits of Ward Undead and a few whacks from your pet will bring down any skeleton, and make you a very viable group member against lesser mummies and zombies, so this is a very powerful spell for necros!<BR>
<BR>
Characters who make undead pets can practice their evocation by casting Ward Undead on their pets, but this is much more boring, lootless and experience-less as opposed to skeleton-plinking.</font></td></tr></table>
